Buying Tickets

Chef wants to buy tickets for a sports game for K people (including himself).

The stadium has N seats, numbered from 1 to N.
The cost of the i-th seat is Aᵢ rupees.

However, some seats have already been purchased. You are given a binary string S where:

Sᵢ = 1 → the i-th seat is already sold

Sᵢ = 0 → the i-th seat is still available

Chef can buy any available seats (they do not need to be consecutive).

Your task is to determine the minimum total cost for Chef to buy exactly K available seats.

If it is not possible to buy K seats (because fewer than K seats are available), print -1.

Input Format

The first line contains an integer T — number of test cases.

For each test case:

The first line contains two integers N and K — total seats and required seats.

The second line contains N integers: A₁, A₂, …, Aₙ (cost of each seat).

The third line contains a binary string S representing seat availability.

Output Format

For each test case, print the minimum cost required to buy K seats.
If it is impossible, print -1.

Key Idea

Consider only seats where Sᵢ = 0 (available).

From those seats, choose K seats with the smallest costs.

SOLUTION:::

import java.util.*;
import java.lang.*;
import java.io.*;

class Codechef
{
	public static void main (String[] args) throws java.lang.Exception
	{
		Scanner s=new Scanner(System.in);
		int t=s.nextInt();
		while(t-->0){
		    int n=s.nextInt();
		    int k=s.nextInt();
		    int a[]=new int[n];
		    for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
		        a[i]=s.nextInt();
		    }
		   s.nextLine();
		   String str=s.nextLine();
		   int sum=0;
		   ArrayList<Integer>mp=new
		       ArrayList<>();
		   for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
		     char ch=str.charAt(i);
		     if(ch=='0'){
		       mp.add(a[i]);
		     }
		   }
		   Collections.sort(mp);
		   if(mp.size()>=k){
	       for(int i=0;i<k;i++){
	          sum+=mp.get(i);
	       }
	       System.out.println(sum);
		   }
		   else{
		       System.out.println("-1");
		   }
		}
	}
}


If available seats < K, output -1.
